        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-12-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-12-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="589" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d589">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24/11–349</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chinese Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Koo</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <p>The Secretary of State presents his compliments to His Excellency the Chinese
                    Ambassador and has the honor to refer to his note dated November 3, 1949
                    regarding the desire of the Chinese Government to obtain certain incendiary
                    bombs, float flares, bomb igniters, and rocket fuzes for use in amphibious
                    defense operations.</p>
                <p>This request is receiving the consideration of the appropriate authories, and it
                    is expected that a final reply will be possible in the near future.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-12-06">December 6,
                            1949</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
